### 7. Observability: Log the Simulation, Do Not Just Summarize

**Problem:** The brainstorm mentions "orchestrator summaries for observability." But after a simulation ends, you want to analyze agent behavior -- who overbid, who was strategic, which personalities worked.

**Recommendation:** Have the orchestrator write a structured log file (JSON lines format) to `tests/sim/results/`:

```jsonl
{"round": 1, "phase": "nomination", "agent": "aggressive_mike", "action": "nominate", "player": "Mahomes", "max_bid": 30}
{"round": 1, "phase": "bidding", "agent": "value_sara", "action": "bid", "player": "Mahomes", "amount": 25}
{"round": 1, "phase": "bidding", "agent": "aggressive_mike", "action": "pass", "player": "Mahomes"}
{"round": 1, "phase": "resolution", "winner": "value_sara", "player": "Mahomes", "price": 25}
```

This is far more useful than prose summaries. It is machine-parseable, allows post-simulation analysis, and can be fed back into agent prompts for future simulations ("In past simulations, aggressive strategies won 60% of top-tier players but overpaid by 15% on average").
